background~
    
{BOLD}{BLACK}   For centuries, Tiwanaku was believed to be folk lore, stories of{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   natives possessing nearly supernatural strength. The men live along{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   the shores of a lake called Titicaca, and the woman live in a city{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   built atop a mountain overlooking the lake. The two groups are{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   separated by a trail guarded by spirits, which only allow the{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   strongest of the males to ascend the trail and mate. If a male lives{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   to reach the top, he would be raped by the woman for a few weeks{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   before sacrificed to the Fertility God. This ensured only the{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   strongest and bravest offspring. Until now, Lake Titicaca and the{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   city of Tiwanaku have been believed to be just tales. But explorers{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   have discovered a group of extraordinarily strong men living on the{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   shores of a relatively unknown lake. No women live amongst these men,{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   but smoke rises from what is believed to be a village sitting on top{bold}
{BOLD}{BLACK}   of a nearby mountain. Could this be the Lost City of Tiwanaku?{bold}

